{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":740,"text":"So, imagine that you had\nyour smartphone miniaturized"},{"time":4443,"text":"and hooked up directly to your brain."},{"time":7711,"text":"If you had this sort of brain chip,"},{"time":9628,"text":"you'd be able to upload\nand download to the internet"},{"time":12183,"text":"at the speed of thought."},{"time":13986,"text":"Accessing social media or Wikipedia\nwould be a lot like --"},{"time":17277,"text":"well, from the inside at least --"},{"time":18941,"text":"like consulting your own memory."},{"time":21247,"text":"It would be as easy\nand as intimate as thinking."},{"time":25579,"text":"But would it make it easier\nfor you to know what's true?"},{"time":28760,"text":"Just because a way\nof accessing information is faster"},{"time":31745,"text":"it doesn't mean it's more\nreliable, of course,"},{"time":34014,"text":"and it doesn't mean that we would all\ninterpret it the same way."},{"time":37269,"text":"And it doesn't mean that you would be\nany better at evaluating it."},{"time":40887,"text":"In fact, you might even be worse,"},{"time":42568,"text":"because, you know, more data,\nless time for evaluation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":46378,"text":"Something like this is already\nhappening to us right now."},{"time":49797,"text":"We already carry a world of information\naround in our pockets,"},{"time":53679,"text":"but it seems as if the more information\nwe share and access online,"},{"time":57932,"text":"the more difficult it can be for us\nto tell the difference"},{"time":60758,"text":"between what's real and what's fake."},{"time":63507,"text":"It's as if we know more\nbut understand less."}]},{"cues":[{"time":68152,"text":"Now, it's a feature\nof modern life, I suppose,"},{"time":71113,"text":"that large swaths of the public\nlive in isolated information bubbles."},{"time":75849,"text":"We're polarized: not just over values,\nbut over the facts."},{"time":80527,"text":"One reason for that is, the data\nanalytics that drive the internet"},{"time":84148,"text":"get us not just more information,"},{"time":86571,"text":"but more of the information that we want."},{"time":88781,"text":"Our online life is personalized;"},{"time":91195,"text":"everything from the ads we read"},{"time":92949,"text":"to the news that comes down\nour Facebook feed"},{"time":95563,"text":"is tailored to satisfy our preferences."},{"time":99279,"text":"And so while we get more information,"},{"time":101109,"text":"a lot of that information ends up\nreflecting ourselves"},{"time":104363,"text":"as much as it does reality."},{"time":107198,"text":"It ends up, I suppose,"},{"time":109691,"text":"inflating our bubbles\nrather than bursting them."},{"time":113331,"text":"And so maybe it's no surprise"},{"time":115484,"text":"that we're in a situation,\na paradoxical situation,"},{"time":118413,"text":"of thinking that we know so much more,"},{"time":120568,"text":"and yet not agreeing\non what it is we know."}]},{"cues":[{"time":125259,"text":"So how are we going to solve\nthis problem of knowledge polarization?"},{"time":128855,"text":"One obvious tactic is to try\nto fix our technology,"},{"time":133047,"text":"to redesign our digital platforms,"},{"time":134980,"text":"so as to make them less\nsusceptible to polarization."},{"time":138884,"text":"And I'm happy to report"},{"time":140107,"text":"that many smart people at Google\nand Facebook are working on just that."},{"time":144771,"text":"And these projects are vital."},{"time":147837,"text":"I think that fixing technology\nis obviously really important,"},{"time":150991,"text":"but I don't think technology alone,\nfixing it, is going to solve the problem"},{"time":155637,"text":"of knowledge polarization."},{"time":157015,"text":"I don't think that because I don't think,\nat the end of the day,"},{"time":160114,"text":"it is a technological problem."},{"time":161767,"text":"I think it's a human problem,"},{"time":163666,"text":"having to do with how we think\nand what we value."}]},{"cues":[{"time":168285,"text":"In order to solve it, I think\nwe're going to need help."},{"time":170924,"text":"We're going to need help\nfrom psychology and political science."},{"time":173953,"text":"But we're also going to need help,\nI think, from philosophy."},{"time":178663,"text":"Because to solve the problem\nof knowledge polarization,"},{"time":183522,"text":"we're going to need to reconnect"},{"time":186455,"text":"with one fundamental, philosophical idea:"},{"time":191219,"text":"that we live in a common reality."},{"time":194671,"text":"The idea of a common reality\nis like, I suppose,"},{"time":198722,"text":"a lot of philosophical concepts:"},{"time":200309,"text":"easy to state"},{"time":201499,"text":"but mysteriously difficult\nto put into practice."},{"time":205003,"text":"To really accept it,"},{"time":206332,"text":"I think we need to do three things,"},{"time":208573,"text":"each of which is a challenge right now."}]},{"cues":[{"time":212749,"text":"First, we need to believe in truth."},{"time":216267,"text":"You might have noticed"},{"time":217454,"text":"that our culture is having\nsomething of a troubled relationship"},{"time":220493,"text":"with that concept right now."},{"time":223061,"text":"It seems as if we disagree so much that,"},{"time":226298,"text":"as one political commentator\nput it not long ago,"},{"time":229131,"text":"it's as if there are no facts anymore."},{"time":232986,"text":"But that thought is actually an expression"},{"time":237232,"text":"of a sort of seductive line\nof argument that's in the air."},{"time":241668,"text":"It goes like this:"},{"time":244188,"text":"we just can't step outside\nof our own perspectives;"},{"time":247063,"text":"we can't step outside of our biases."},{"time":249529,"text":"Every time we try,"},{"time":251026,"text":"we just get more information\nfrom our perspective."},{"time":255536,"text":"So, this line of thought goes,"},{"time":259016,"text":"we might as well admit\nthat objective truth is an illusion,"},{"time":262802,"text":"or it doesn't matter,"},{"time":263980,"text":"because either we'll never\nknow what it is,"},{"time":267039,"text":"or it doesn't exist in the first place."}]},{"cues":[{"time":271173,"text":"That's not a new philosophical thought --"},{"time":274193,"text":"skepticism about truth."},{"time":277332,"text":"During the end of the last century,\nas some of you know,"},{"time":280237,"text":"it was very popular in certain\nacademic circles."},{"time":283317,"text":"But it really goes back all the way\nto the Greek philosopher Protagoras,"},{"time":288474,"text":"if not farther back."},{"time":290252,"text":"Protagoras said that objective\ntruth was an illusion"},{"time":292725,"text":"because \"man is the measure\nof all things.\""},{"time":295656,"text":"Man is the measure of all things."},{"time":298169,"text":"That can seem like a bracing bit\nof realpolitik to people,"},{"time":301016,"text":"or liberating,"},{"time":302199,"text":"because it allows each of us\nto discover or make our own truth."}]},{"cues":[{"time":308618,"text":"But actually, I think it's a bit\nof self-serving rationalization"},{"time":312804,"text":"disguised as philosophy."},{"time":315507,"text":"It confuses the difficulty\nof being certain"},{"time":318339,"text":"with the impossibility of truth."},{"time":322223,"text":"Look --"},{"time":324768,"text":"of course it's difficult\nto be certain about anything;"},{"time":328908,"text":"we might all be living in \"The Matrix.\""},{"time":332018,"text":"You might have a brain chip in your head"},{"time":334024,"text":"feeding you all the wrong information."},{"time":337593,"text":"But in practice, we do agree\non all sorts of facts."},{"time":341796,"text":"We agree that bullets can kill people."},{"time":345616,"text":"We agree that you can't flap\nyour arms and fly."},{"time":350023,"text":"We agree -- or we should --"},{"time":353018,"text":"that there is an external reality"},{"time":355339,"text":"and ignoring it can get you hurt."}]},{"cues":[{"time":359205,"text":"Nonetheless, skepticism\nabout truth can be tempting,"},{"time":363378,"text":"because it allows us to rationalize\naway our own biases."},{"time":366716,"text":"When we do that, we're sort of like\nthe guy in the movie"},{"time":369727,"text":"who knew he was living in \"The Matrix\""},{"time":372793,"text":"but decided he liked it there, anyway."},{"time":377031,"text":"After all, getting what you\nwant feels good."},{"time":380271,"text":"Being right all the time feels good."},{"time":382991,"text":"So, often it's easier for us"},{"time":385797,"text":"to wrap ourselves in our cozy\ninformation bubbles,"},{"time":390049,"text":"live in bad faith,"},{"time":391614,"text":"and take those bubbles\nas the measure of reality."}]},{"cues":[{"time":396595,"text":"An example, I think, of how\nthis bad faith gets into our action"},{"time":402464,"text":"is our reaction\nto the phenomenon of fake news."},{"time":407874,"text":"The fake news that spread on the internet"},{"time":410828,"text":"during the American\npresidential election of 2016"},{"time":415506,"text":"was designed to feed into our biases,"},{"time":418157,"text":"designed to inflate our bubbles."},{"time":420295,"text":"But what was really striking about it"},{"time":422370,"text":"was not just that it fooled\nso many people."},{"time":425595,"text":"What was really striking to me\nabout fake news,"},{"time":428460,"text":"the phenomenon,"},{"time":429822,"text":"is how quickly it itself became\nthe subject of knowledge polarization;"},{"time":435582,"text":"so much so, that the very term --\nthe very term -- \"fake news\""},{"time":439285,"text":"now just means: \"news story I don't like.\""},{"time":443367,"text":"That's an example of the bad faith\ntowards the truth that I'm talking about."}]},{"cues":[{"time":451240,"text":"But the really, I think, dangerous thing"},{"time":455981,"text":"about skepticism with regard to truth"},{"time":459476,"text":"is that it leads to despotism."},{"time":462350,"text":"\"Man is the measure of all things\""},{"time":465297,"text":"inevitably becomes \"The Man\nis the measure of all things.\""},{"time":469852,"text":"Just as \"every man for himself\""},{"time":472526,"text":"always seems to turn out to be\n\"only the strong survive.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":476345,"text":"At the end of Orwell's \"1984,\""},{"time":480136,"text":"the thought policeman O'Brien is torturing\nthe protagonist Winston Smith"},{"time":484419,"text":"into believing two plus two equals five."},{"time":488571,"text":"What O'Brien says is the point,"},{"time":493486,"text":"is that he wants to convince Smith\nthat whatever the party says is the truth,"},{"time":497931,"text":"and the truth is whatever the party says."},{"time":501484,"text":"And what O'Brien knows\nis that once this thought is accepted,"},{"time":506387,"text":"critical dissent is impossible."},{"time":509857,"text":"You can't speak truth to power"},{"time":512069,"text":"if the power speaks truth by definition."}]},{"cues":[{"time":516880,"text":"I said that in order to accept\nthat we really live in a common reality,"},{"time":521147,"text":"we have to do three things."},{"time":522458,"text":"The first thing is to believe in truth."},{"time":524467,"text":"The second thing can be summed up"},{"time":526161,"text":"by the Latin phrase that Kant took\nas the motto for the Enlightenment:"},{"time":531271,"text":"\"Sapere aude,\""},{"time":532932,"text":"or \"dare to know.\""},{"time":534688,"text":"Or as Kant wants,\n\"to dare to know for yourself.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":538208,"text":"I think in the early days of the internet,"},{"time":540274,"text":"a lot of us thought"},{"time":541464,"text":"that information technology\nwas always going to make it easier"},{"time":545298,"text":"for us to know for ourselves,"},{"time":547177,"text":"and of course in many ways, it has."},{"time":549893,"text":"But as the internet has become\nmore and more a part of our lives,"},{"time":553755,"text":"our reliance on it, our use of it,"},{"time":555738,"text":"has become often more passive."},{"time":558322,"text":"Much of what we know today we Google-know."},{"time":561299,"text":"We download prepackaged sets of facts"},{"time":565018,"text":"and sort of shuffle them along\nthe assembly line of social media."},{"time":569357,"text":"Now, Google-knowing is useful"},{"time":570811,"text":"precisely because it involves\na sort of intellectual outsourcing."},{"time":574031,"text":"We offload our effort onto a network\nof others and algorithms."},{"time":579820,"text":"And that allows us, of course,\nto not clutter our minds"},{"time":582851,"text":"with all sorts of facts."},{"time":584314,"text":"We can just download them\nwhen we need them."},{"time":586625,"text":"And that's awesome."}]},{"cues":[{"time":589348,"text":"But there's a difference\nbetween downloading a set of facts"},{"time":594809,"text":"and really understanding how or why\nthose facts are as they are."},{"time":601237,"text":"Understanding why\na particular disease spreads,"},{"time":605635,"text":"or how a mathematical proof works,"},{"time":607718,"text":"or why your friend is depressed,"},{"time":609755,"text":"involves more than just downloading."},{"time":613396,"text":"It's going to require, most likely,"},{"time":615501,"text":"doing some work for yourself:"},{"time":618503,"text":"having a little creative insight;"},{"time":620367,"text":"using your imagination;"},{"time":621657,"text":"getting out into the field;"},{"time":622999,"text":"doing the experiment;"},{"time":624205,"text":"working through the proof;"},{"time":625500,"text":"talking to someone."}]},{"cues":[{"time":631533,"text":"Now, I'm not saying, of course,\nthat we should stop Google-knowing."},{"time":636402,"text":"I'm just saying"},{"time":637577,"text":"we shouldn't overvalue it, either."},{"time":639287,"text":"We need to find ways of encouraging\nforms of knowing that are more active,"},{"time":644512,"text":"and don't always involve passing off\nour effort into our bubble."},{"time":650242,"text":"Because the thing about Google-knowing\nis that too often it ends up"},{"time":653607,"text":"being bubble-knowing."},{"time":655581,"text":"And bubble-knowing means\nalways being right."},{"time":659183,"text":"But daring to know,"},{"time":661404,"text":"daring to understand,"},{"time":664151,"text":"means risking the possibility\nthat you could be wrong."},{"time":667921,"text":"It means risking the possibility"},{"time":670213,"text":"that what you want and what's true\nare different things."}]},{"cues":[{"time":676070,"text":"Which brings me to the third thing\nthat I think we need to do"},{"time":679854,"text":"if we want to accept that we live\nin a common reality."},{"time":682910,"text":"That third thing is:\nhave a little humility."},{"time":686510,"text":"By humility here, I mean\nepistemic humility,"},{"time":688656,"text":"which means, in a sense,"},{"time":691701,"text":"knowing that you don't know it all."},{"time":694128,"text":"But it also means something\nmore than that."},{"time":696205,"text":"It means seeing your worldview\nas open to improvement"},{"time":700679,"text":"by the evidence and experience of others."},{"time":702834,"text":"Seeing your worldview\nas open to improvement"},{"time":704907,"text":"by the evidence and experience of others."},{"time":708084,"text":"That's more than just\nbeing open to change."},{"time":710147,"text":"It's more than just being open\nto self-improvement."},{"time":712569,"text":"It means seeing your knowledge\nas capable of enhancing"},{"time":716878,"text":"or being enriched\nby what others contribute."},{"time":720224,"text":"That's part of what is involved"},{"time":722962,"text":"in recognizing there's a common reality"},{"time":726116,"text":"that you, too, are responsible to."}]},{"cues":[{"time":729633,"text":"I don't think it's much\nof a stretch to say"},{"time":731862,"text":"that our society is not particularly great\nat enhancing or encouraging"},{"time":736841,"text":"that sort of humility."},{"time":738080,"text":"That's partly because,"},{"time":740810,"text":"well, we tend to confuse\narrogance and confidence."},{"time":744263,"text":"And it's partly because, well, you know,"},{"time":747341,"text":"arrogance is just easier."},{"time":748918,"text":"It's just easier to think of yourself\nas knowing it all."},{"time":751619,"text":"It's just easier to think of yourself\nas having it all figured out."},{"time":756513,"text":"But that's another example\nof the bad faith towards the truth"},{"time":759470,"text":"that I've been talking about."}]},{"cues":[{"time":763391,"text":"So the concept of a common reality,"},{"time":765652,"text":"like a lot of philosophical concepts,"},{"time":768366,"text":"can seem so obvious,"},{"time":770785,"text":"that we can look right past it"},{"time":773945,"text":"and forget why it's important."},{"time":777394,"text":"Democracies can't function\nif their citizens don't strive,"},{"time":782362,"text":"at least some of the time,"},{"time":783756,"text":"to inhabit a common space,"},{"time":785461,"text":"a space where they can pass\nideas back and forth"},{"time":790123,"text":"when -- and especially when --"},{"time":791933,"text":"they disagree."},{"time":793749,"text":"But you can't strive to inhabit that space"},{"time":797560,"text":"if you don't already accept\nthat you live in the same reality."},{"time":803144,"text":"To accept that, we've got\nto believe in truth,"},{"time":805339,"text":"we've got to encourage\nmore active ways of knowing."},{"time":809394,"text":"And we've got to have the humility"},{"time":812271,"text":"to realize that we're not\nthe measure of all things."}]},{"cues":[{"time":817049,"text":"We may yet one day realize the vision"},{"time":820597,"text":"of having the internet in our brains."},{"time":824545,"text":"But if we want that to be liberating\nand not terrifying,"},{"time":828488,"text":"if we want it to expand our understanding"},{"time":831274,"text":"and not just our passive knowing,"},{"time":834585,"text":"we need to remember that our perspectives,"},{"time":838248,"text":"as wondrous, as beautiful as they are,"},{"time":842171,"text":"are just that --"},{"time":843475,"text":"perspectives on one reality."}]},{"cues":[{"time":847096,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":848391,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}